			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>COPE – A Workbench for the Coupled Evolution of Metamodels and Models</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MarkusHerrmannsdörfer.html">Markus Herrmannsdörfer</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_18">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_18</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> COPE is presented as a workbench/tool to support coupled evolution workflows.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagL">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> Its purpose is to manage evolution/maintenance by coordinating metamodel changes with model migrations.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The workbench operationalizes evolution via reusable migration operations/transformations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
